From: Til Kaiser <mail@tk154.de>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 12:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ath12k: allow DT board_id override for board data selection

Some PCIe ath12k platforms report an unusable board ID (0xff) from
OTP/QMI, which makes firmware lookup fall back to
`bus=pci,qmi-chip-id=...,qmi-board-id=255` and miss the intended board
entry.

Add a Device Tree override path for board ID in both MHI and QMI flows:
- in `ath12k_mhi_register()`, prefer `board_id` from DT when present,
  otherwise keep existing OTP register fallback.
- in `ath12k_qmi_request_target_cap()`, prefer `board_id` from DT when
  present, otherwise keep existing QMI/default behavior.

This keeps current behavior for existing targets while allowing boards to
provide a stable board ID through DTS for correct board-2.bin matching.

This DT-based board_id override follows the downstream Qualcomm/QSDK
approach.

Signed-off-by: Til Kaiser <mail@tk154.de>
---

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mhi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mhi.c
@@ -334,9 +334,11 @@ int ath12k_mhi_register(struct ath12k_pc
 	mhi_ctrl->rddm_size = ab->hw_params->rddm_size;
 
 	if (ab->hw_params->otp_board_id_register) {
-		board_id =
-			ath12k_pci_read32(ab, ab->hw_params->otp_board_id_register);
-		board_id = u32_get_bits(board_id, OTP_BOARD_ID_MASK);
+		if (of_property_read_u32(ab->dev->of_node, "board_id", &board_id)) {
+			board_id =
+				ath12k_pci_read32(ab, ab->hw_params->otp_board_id_register);
+			board_id = u32_get_bits(board_id, OTP_BOARD_ID_MASK);
+		}
 
 		if (!board_id || (board_id == OTP_INVALID_BOARD_ID)) {
 			ath12k_dbg(ab, ATH12K_DBG_BOOT,
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/qmi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/qmi.c
@@ -2814,7 +2814,8 @@ int ath12k_qmi_request_target_cap(struct
 	struct qmi_wlanfw_cap_req_msg_v01 req = {};
 	struct qmi_wlanfw_cap_resp_msg_v01 resp = {};
 	struct qmi_txn txn;
-	unsigned int board_id = ATH12K_BOARD_ID_DEFAULT;
+	struct device *dev = ab->dev;
+	unsigned int board_id;
 	int ret = 0;
 	int r;
 	int i;
@@ -2853,10 +2854,12 @@ int ath12k_qmi_request_target_cap(struct
 		ab->qmi.target.chip_family = resp.chip_info.chip_family;
 	}
 
-	if (resp.board_info_valid)
+	if (!of_property_read_u32(dev->of_node, "board_id", &board_id))
+		ab->qmi.target.board_id = board_id;
+	else if (resp.board_info_valid)
 		ab->qmi.target.board_id = resp.board_info.board_id;
 	else
-		ab->qmi.target.board_id = board_id;
+		ab->qmi.target.board_id = ATH12K_BOARD_ID_DEFAULT;
 
 	if (resp.soc_info_valid)
 		ab->qmi.target.soc_id = resp.soc_info.soc_id;
